# Sero — agent orientation

Sero is a **1:1 prep engine**: given a manager + a report + a meeting type, it runs a
5-stage LLM pipeline that produces focus points, a preparation brief, interview questions,
drives the conversation turn by turn, and writes a post-meeting briefing.

**This file is deliberately thin.** The last version duplicated project state and went
badly stale (it described a pre-monorepo layout that no longer exists). Don't add
point-in-time state here — it belongs in the trackers below.

## The real map (as of 2026-07)

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| Engine (the product) | `backend/engine/` — public facade `backend/engine/index.ts` |
| Pipeline stages (5) | focus-points → preparation → question-bank → planner loop → evaluation. Full map: `docs/reference/engine-map.md` |
| The two orchestrators | web: `backend/api/services/sessions/session-streams.ts` · CLI: `backend/engine/cli/stages/*` — **they must move in lockstep** |
| API server | `backend/api/` (controller → service → co-located repo) |
| Typed contracts | `backend/shared/*.types.ts` |
| Prompts | `content/prompts/` (per-type overlays in `backend/engine/one-on-one-types/`) |
| What "correct" means | deterministic gates in `evals/trust-checks.ts` + `backend/engine/golden-checks.ts`, proven against ratified cases in `evals/golden/` |
| Admin console | `admin/` (Vite) · customer app: `frontend/` |

## Rules that always apply

1. **Read `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root first** — it is the authoritative behavioral spec
   (surgical changes, simplicity, the Darren Method, reply format, standing rules).
2. **Where are we?** `STATUS.md` (tactical) + `SERO_BOARD.md` (strategic). Never trust
   this file or old plans for state.
3. **Cost:** free checks first (`npm test`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`,
   `node scripts/replay-scenario.js <id> --fixtures-only`). Anything hitting the OpenAI
   API (`npm run gate` / `smoke` / `eval` judge / persona runs) costs real money —
   one paid run per task max, smallest possible proof, state the cost first.
4. **Engine honesty:** surface raw model output; detect problems and flag them — never
   hardcode text rewrites to hide them.
5. **New code is TypeScript (strict), test-first.** Conventions:
   `.claude/skills/backend-conventions/` and `.claude/skills/frontend-conventions/`.

## Build / run / verify

```bash
npm run dev        # api + vite web app
npm test           # full offline suite (free, no API key)
npm run typecheck  # strict TS, backend; typecheck:admin for the console
npm run gate       # PAID golden-set regression — ask before running
```
